      <p class="subhead">Notes on the Saxon implementation</p>
      <p>Saxon allows the first argument to be an empty sequence, treating this as equivalent
	    to calling fn:error() with no arguments. The error code (local part and namespace URI part) is
	    recorded as part of the exception that's supplied to a user-defined JAXP <code>ErrorListener</code>,
	    or that is returned to the calling application. The value of the <code>$description</code>
    is available by calling <code>getMessage()</code> on the <code>Exception</code> object.
      The error details are also available to the <code>catch</code>
	    part of a call when using the XQuery 3.0 or XSLT 3.0 try/catch construct.</p>
